@node "requerimentos" "Requeriments"

 @{b}hardware and OS:@{ub}

 - Amiga OS 1.3 (theorically) - tested with Amiga OS 2.1 and 3.0

 - 68000, few kb of memory    - tested with 000, 030

 - serial port, serial.device compatible. - tested with 8n1 and serial.


 @{b}extra software:@{ub}

 - TCP-IP network installed and running.

 - SANA-II PPP driver activatable/deactivatable by CLI commands, in
   SHARED mode.


 @{b}if you want to use BBS support you also need:@{ub}

 - Max's BBS + MAXsTD (patch for using Trap Door with Max's, which enables
serial.device shared-mode in Max's and permmits AIP runing with BBS).
   (well, perhaps you may use other BBS software, but frankly i don't
remember for sure how AIP treats this... it wasn't that important since the
client who wanted this never confirmed, so i made the minimum for working)

@endnode

