@node "compilando" "Compiling AIP"

   There's no secrets about this, just copy the following files:

   AmigaInetProvider.pascal   - main part, includes serial routines
   ControleUsuarios.pascal    - user database and configuration management.

   ..to your work directory.

   And compile the AmigaInetProvider.pascal, which will include
automatically the ControleUsuarios.pascal in the compiling process.

   This software can be sucessfully compiled with @{b}HS Pascal 1.10 and 1.20@{ub}.


   There's TWO sources of AIP: the original one and the newer one, with
minor modifications. This is because the original one refused to compile
when i tried recently (no idea why, AFAIR these sources were in a
compileable state last time i modified them, over two years ago).

   In case there's some problem with my corrections (i don't think so), you
can always try compiling the old sources.



   The listings are fully commented, but in portuguese (why the hell would i
in english?) since they weren't aimed for being freely available. Perhaps
someday i'll upload a translated version.

   You'll notice the other files in AIP are in english, that's because i was
thinking about the possibility of releasing AIP for public.

@endnode

